==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eavesdropping
<hw>Eaves"drop`ping</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>The habit of lurking about dwelling houses, and other places where
persons meet for private intercourse, secretly listening to what is
said, and then tattling it abroad. The offense is indictable at common
law.</def> <rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ebb</ent>⟦br⟧
